# Cosmon runtime noise — durable markdown artifacts (synthesis.md,
# outcomes.md, briefing.md, notes/**, responses/**, scan.md,
# triage-report.md, analysis.md) and events.jsonl ARE tracked.
registry.sqlite
registry.sqlite-journal
registry.sqlite-wal
*.lock
*.tmp

# Top-level runtime logs (cs run / watchdog / one-off fix logs). These are
# transient noise — never source of truth — and previously leaked into the
# tracked surface (one carried a client worker name). Source of cognitive
# history is events.jsonl, not these. Ignore at the .cosmon root.
*.log

# Runtime state — selective: ignore ephemeral/binary, track markdown.
#
# state.json is a DERIVABLE CACHE rebuilt by `cs reconcile` from events.jsonl.
# events.jsonl is the SOURCE OF TRUTH for cognitive history (seals included).
# Crossing the cache across a residence boundary creates a two-clock paradox
# (hawking: chronology protection); crossing only the log preserves seals.
# See docs/architectural-invariants.md §9 and synthesis at
# .cosmon/state/fleets/default/molecules/delib-20260420-0469/synthesis.md (R4).
state/fleet.json
state/fleet.runtime.json
state/**/state.json
state/**/runtime.lock
state/**/*.lock
state/**/*.pid
state/**/pty.log
state/**/tmux-capture.log
state/**/*.log
